gomodel:SYNGO_4875  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 4: Immunoelectron microscopic detection of double immunogold labeling by antisera against VGLUT1 and Gβ2 (GNB2) showed localization of both to synaptic vesicles.. Experimental description: M&M: \"Deeply anesthesized rats were sacrificed by decapitation. The cerebellar cortex was immediately removed and cut into small cubes of about 8 mm3\"\n\nantibody:\n\"The following rabbit polyclonal antisera against G-protein subtypes were used: ... Gβ2 (AS 36; Hinsch et al., 1989) ... All G-protein subtype-specific antisera were characterized for immunocytochemistry with respect to specificity and crossreactivity (Brunk et al., 1999; this paper).\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2022-09-11" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4875" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
